## Phase 0 — Foundation (3 hours, day 1 morning)

**Goal:** Everything is set up so the team can build without setup friction.

Tasks:
- Provision Vultr VM (Ubuntu 24, 4 vCPU / 8GB), point a domain at it, install Docker + Caddy
- Create the GitHub repo with a sane structure: `/backend`, `/frontend`, `/infra`, `/demo-assets`, `README.md`
- Set up Gemini API access; verify a hello-world call from a Python script using the official `google-genai` SDK
- Configure environment variables (Gemini key, Tavily key, allowed origins) loaded from `.env`
- Deploy a placeholder FastAPI + Next.js app to Vultr with HTTPS; verify the full pipeline works end-to-end with a "hello world" round-trip

**Definition of done:** A judge can hit `https://your-domain.com`, see a placeholder page, and the backend can call Gemini Pro. Verified live, not just locally.

**Why this matters:** Most hackathon teams discover deployment issues at hour 40, when it's too late. Deploy first, then iterate. Every commit afterward should auto-deploy or have a one-command deploy script.

