## Phase 3 — Multimodal inputs (5 hours, day 2) - to be reviewed by claude

**Goal:** Real input handling — PDFs, images, URLs — feeding into the workspace before agents run.

### PDF upload (1.5 hours)

- Frontend dropzone, `POST /sessions/{id}/inputs/document` with multipart upload
- Backend uses PyMuPDF to extract text + page-rendered images of any pages with charts/tables
- Charts/tables get sent to Gemini Vision in a separate call to extract structured data ("describe this chart as a table")
- Extracted content goes to `workspace.inputs.documents`

### Whiteboard / image upload (1.5 hours)

- Same dropzone, image goes straight to Gemini Vision with a prompt: *"This is a photo of a whiteboard sketch related to a business decision. Extract every readable element — text, arrows, boxes, numbers — and describe the relationships."*
- Output goes to `workspace.inputs.raw_text` with a marker indicating it came from a whiteboard
- **This is your demo gold moment.** Make sure it works perfectly with one specific test image you'll use in the demo.

### URL paste (1 hour)

- Frontend text field accepting a URL
- Backend uses a simple fetch + BeautifulSoup or Trafilatura to extract main article content
- Content goes to `workspace.inputs.documents` with the source URL preserved
- Have a fallback to pre-cached content if the live fetch fails (network issues during demos are common)

### Pre-staged demo bundle (1 hour)

- Create a "Load demo scenario: TargetCo Acquisition" button on the upload screen
- One click loads three real inputs (deck PDF, whiteboard photo, TechCrunch article URL) and starts the analysis
- This is what you'll click 95% of the time during demos. Live uploads are for "look, it really works with arbitrary inputs."

**Definition of done:** A judge can drop in a PDF, drag in a whiteboard photo, paste a URL, click Analyze, and watch all five agents start working on real data.

**Cut if behind:** Drop the URL paste feature first (least demo value). Drop whiteboard photo second (sad — it's the wow moment). Never drop PDF upload.

