## Cut list if you're behind (in priority order to cut)

1. Sound effects, advanced animations
2. URL paste input (keep PDF + image)
3. Whiteboard image input (sad but recoverable)
4. Visual conflict highlighting (huge loss — try hard not to cut)
5. Real parallel orchestration (fall back to sequential with fake parallelism in UI)
6. Live web search (use cached results entirely)

Things you should **never** cut:
- The five visible agent panels
- Streaming text via SSE
- The polished final brief
- Vultr deployment
- The pre-staged demo scenario

