## Risk register (in order of likelihood)

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| Demo network unreliable on stage | High | Local cached fallback, demo mode toggle, mobile hotspot backup |
| Gemini API rate limits or latency spikes | Medium | Pre-warm, demo-mode caching, retry with exponential backoff |
| One agent crashes mid-demo | Medium | Each agent in a `try/except` that emits a graceful error event; orchestrator continues with remaining agents |
| Vultr deployment hiccup hours before pitch | Medium | Mirror to Render or Railway as backup; have one-command redeploy ready |
| Demo runs over time | Medium | Pre-time it; the brief should appear by 2:00; have a "final summary" version of the demo if cut to 1 minute |
| Judges ask whether agents are "real" or fake | Low | Show the GitHub repo with separate prompt files; show network tab with parallel API calls; show the blackboard state |

---

## North star reminder

The product is the **visible, structured disagreement** between specialized agents working toward a defensible decision. Every choice in this build — architecture, UI, demo — should make that more visible, not less. If a feature doesn't help a judge see five intelligent agents collaborating and disagreeing, it's a distraction. Cut accordingly.